      '<p class="ql-align-justify"><a href="https://oec.world/en/profile/bilateral-country/ind/partner/ita" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);">The Trade Trend</a><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">: Over the past 5 years the exports of India to Italy have increased at an annualized rate of 32%, from $1.48B in 2017 to $5.92B in 2022.</span></p><p><a href="https://www.indiatvnews.com/explainers/how-have-india-italy-relations-strengthened-under-pm-modi-giorgia-meloni-g7-summit-2024-rome-updates-2024-06-14-936905" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);">The Charm of #MELODI</a><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">: Bilateral relations between India and Italy have witnessed an upswing under the leadership of PM Modi and his Italian counterpart Giorgia Meloni </span></p>',
    editor: '',
    excerpt:
      '“Hello from Melodi Team” said Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni in her buoyant video selfie with Prime Minister Narendra Modi at the G7 meeting. India-Italy relations soar to new heights with an expansive roadmap for bilateral cooperation.',

    expires: '',
    genre: ['world'],
    headline: 'The Melodi Equation',
