    metaDescription:
      "Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to Italy for the G7 Summit marked his first international trip after commencing his third term. Invited by Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, PM Modi's presence at this prestigious gathering underscores India's pivotal role in global affairs. ",
    metaTitle: "India's Leadership Shines at G7 Summit",
    name: "India's Leadership Shines at G7 Summit",
    pageContent:
      "<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to Italy for the G7 Summit marked his first international trip after commencing his third term. Invited by Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, PM Modi's presence at this prestigious gathering underscores India's pivotal role in global affairs. The G7, comprising the world's most advanced economies, addresses pressing international issues through collective action.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">During the summit, PM Modi held bilateral meetings with prominent leaders, including U.S. President Joe Biden, British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak, and French President Emmanuel Macron. His discussions emphasised dismantling technological monopolies and promoting inclusive, innovative growth, particularly in artificial intelligence. PM Modi highlighted India's pioneering efforts in formulating a national AI strategy, advocating for transparency and accountability in AI governance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The summit also saw the G7's endorsement of the India-Middle East-Europe Economic Corridor (IMEC), a transformative infrastructure initiative to enhance global connectivity. This project, seen as a strategic counterbalance to China's Belt and Road Initiative, showcases India's commitment to fostering economic integration and sustainable development.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Prime Minister Modi's proactive engagement at the G7 Summit amplifies India's influence on the world stage and underscores its leadership in driving technological advancements and strategic connectivity projects. His participation reaffirms India's dedication to a free and open Indo-Pacific, and its vision for a collaborative, prosperous global future. India's voice is resounding louder than ever, signalling its ascent as a global powerhouse committed to shaping a better world</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>",
    publishedAt: '2024-06-15T11:41:59.775Z',
