    diveContent:
      '<p><a href="https://swarajyamag.com/culture/what-russian-writers-learnt-from-india" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><strong>‘Volga to Ganges’</strong></a><strong style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">:</strong><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">&nbsp;A number of Russian writers and poets have paid tributes to Vedic philosophy in their writings, and similarly Indian authors like Rahul Sankrityayan imagined India on the Bolshevik model.</span></p><p><a href="https://www.vifindia.org/sites/default/files/Siberia-and-India-Historical-Cultural-Affinities.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><strong>India in Eurasia</strong></a><strong style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">:</strong><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">&nbsp;India has close cultural, social and political linkages with the whole Eurasian region, most especially with Russia, impacting the imaginations of its writers.</span></p><p><a href="https://indiaartreview.com/stories/russia-and-india-historical-friendship/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><strong>Development</strong></a><strong style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">:</strong><span style="background-color: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">&nbsp;Not only inspiring writers in India, Moscow has its long-lasting stamp on India’s development, notes ex-diplomat Achala Moulik in her book.</span></p>',
