      "<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bangladesh's Foreign Minister, Dr. Hasan Mahmud, is on an official visit to India from February 7-9, 2024, following an invitation from his Indian counterpart, Dr. S. Jaishankar. Their discussions on February 7th covered extensive bilateral issues, including enhancing cross-border connectivity, deepening economic and development partnerships, and boosting defence and security cooperation. Additionally, they explored collaboration in sectors like power, energy, and water resources, aiming to align their efforts with India's \"Viksit Bharat 2047\" and Bangladesh's \"Smart Bangladesh 2041\" development visions. This meeting comes on the heels of the recent joint initiatives by Indian PM Narendra Modi and Bangladesh PM Sheikh Hasina, marking a significant step in bilateral relations. The Ministers underscored their commitment to reinforcing sub-regional cooperation through BIMSTEC, IORA, and BBIN frameworks. Dr. Mahmud's visit, the first since Bangladesh's January 2024 elections, symbolises the nation's dedication to fortifying its decades-old and enduring relationship with India, emphasising a mutual interest in expanding trade and development collaborations. Amidst intensifying endeavours to bolster relations, this visit may signal Bangladesh's shift towards overcoming anti-India sentiment, acknowledging India's pivotal role on the global political stage.</span></p>",
