      '<p><a href="https://yourstory.com/2023/11/indian-startups-break-funding-records-in-2022-says-avaana-capital" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;">Favourites for funding</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">: According to Anjali Bansal, the Founding Partner of Avaana Capital, startups dedicated to combating climate change in India secured $2.2 billion in funding.&nbsp;</span></p><p><a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/climate-finance-technology-extremely-essential-to-fulfil-aspirations-of-global-south-pm-modi/articleshow/105660470.cms" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;">Key to Action</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">: At COP 28 held in Dubai, Indian Prime Minister Modi emphasises the importance of climate tech for the global south and its strive in climate action.</span></p><p><a href="https://www.asiaone.com/business/green-gold-india-and-southeast-asias-climate-tech-sector-projected-hit-350-billion-2030" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;">Hopes and Projections</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">: A recent report by Golden Gate Ventures stated that India and Southeast Asia\'s Climate Tech Sector Projected to Hit $350 Billion by 2030.</span></p>',
