      "In a notable diplomatic event, H.E. Dr. Vincent Biruta, the Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation of the Republic of Rwanda, visited India from December 7-8, 2023. This visit aimed to strengthen bilateral ties and explore collaboration opportunities between the two nations. External Affairs Minister, Dr. S. Jaishankar, engaged in delegation-level talks with Minister Biruta. The discussions covered the entire spectrum of bilateral relations, including regional and international issues, and cooperation in multilateral fora.    H.E. Dr. Vincent Biruta's visit exemplifies the commitment of both nations to strengthen diplomatic ties. The delegation-level talks reflect the depth and significance of the relationship between India and Rwanda. As the visit concludes, it leaves behind the promise of enhanced cooperation and a brighter future for the diplomatic relations between these two nations.",
    metaTitle:
      'India-Myanmar FOC: Strengthening Bilateral Ties and Realising Democratic Aspirations',
    name: 'India-Myanmar FOC: Strengthening Bilateral Ties and Realising Democratic Aspirations',
    pageContent:
      '<p class="ql-align-justify"><br></p><p class="ql-align-justify"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">New Delhi played host to the 20th round of India-Myanmar Foreign Office Consultations (FOC) on December 6, 2023. The discussions were led by Foreign Secretary Shri Vinay Kwatra from India and Deputy Foreign Minister of Myanmar, U Lwin Oo, the consultations provided a platform for both delegations to engage in discussions covering a broad spectrum of issues. Addressing shared concerns related to transnational crimes was a crucial aspect of the discussions. Both delegations explored collaborative measures to tackle these challenges, emphasising the importance of joint efforts in maintaining regional security.</span></p><p class="ql-align-justify"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">India reiterated its unwavering support to Myanmar as it transitions towards a federal democracy. This commitment shows India\'s dedication to the democratic aspirations of its neighbour. The Indian delegation expressed continued support for people-centric socio-economic developmental projects in Myanmar. This encompasses various initiatives, including connectivity projects and those under the Rakhine State Development Programme and Border Area Development Programme, aimed at benefiting the citizens of Myanmar.</span></p><p><br></p><p class="ql-align-justify"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;">As India continues to stand by Myanmar in its journey towards a federal democracy, the collaborative efforts discussed in the FOC underscore the depth and breadth of the strategic partnership between these neighbouring countries.</span></p>',
