    excerpt:
      "\nNepali mercenaries are being enlisted by the Russian army for war against Ukraine. On October 14, 2023, eight Nepali citizens arrived in Russia, seeking employment. In early November, while in Moscow, they entered into contracts with the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation, agreeing to join the Northern Military District. Subsequently, they were assigned to a unit within the 58th Combined Arms Army of the Russian Federation, specifically Military Unit 47084 in North Ossetia. Here are their names, birthdates, ranks, and roles:\n\n\n\nKhadka Chetendra, born on April 29, 1979 - Private, Grenade Launcher.\nAdhikari Yubraj, born on October 6, 1979 - Private, Machine Gunner.\nBishwakarma Lal Bahadur, born on May 8, 1983 - Private, Senior Rifleman.\nBishwakarma Tilak Bahadur, born on August 5, 1989 - Private, Machine Gunner.\nKhadka Deepak, born on July 26, 1998 - Private, Grenade Launcher.\nBhattarai Laxman, born on July 26, 1982 - Private, Machine Gunner.\nPahadi Jagadish, born on July 22, 1984 - Private, Senior Rifleman.\nRahapal Sushant Kumar, born on June 17, 1992 - Private, Rifleman.\n\n\nUpon signing their initial contracts with the RF Armed Forces, each of them received 195,000 rubles. Remarkably, they managed to reach the unit stationed in the Rostov region. However, these individuals decided that it wasn't worth risking their lives. Without even serving two weeks, on the night of November 16-17, 2023, all eight Nepalese escaped from the unit's location. A search was initiated, and they were charged with Article 337 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation, which pertains to unauthorized abandonment of a military unit. As of December 1, 2023, they remained elusive, with strong indications that they had already left the territory of the Russian Federation.",

