    excerpt:
      "Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas has stated that Hamas's policies and actions do not reflect the sentiments of the Palestinian people. Numerous entities, including the UN, European Union, USA, UK, Canada, Japan, Australia, the Organization of American States, Egypt, and Jordan, categorize Hamas as a terrorist organization. #HAMAS does not speak for #Palestinians. In many countries, Hamas is a banned terrorist entity. In these nations, citizens can face legal consequences for the following actions related to Hamas:\n\n\n\nMembership in Hamas.\nSoliciting support for Hamas.\nVoicing support for Hamas while recklessly disregarding the possibility that such expressions might encourage further support.\nOrganizing gatherings in support of Hamas.\nPublicly wearing clothing or carrying items that might reasonably suggest an association with or support for Hamas.\nDisplaying symbols associated with Hamas, such as flags or logos, especially if it could reasonably suggest affiliation or support.\n\n\nSeparately, Noor Dahri, the Executive Director of the Islamic Theology of Counter Terrorism (ITCT) – a UK-based counter Islamist terrorism think tank – has disclosed that the Liwa #Zainebiyoun Brigade, an Iranian-backed militia primarily comprised of Pakistani Shias, is recruiting Pakistani Shia individuals via a Telegram channel to engage in combat in #Palestine. [Source]",

