    excerpt:
      "Dr. Rajkumar Ranjan Singh, Minister of State for External Affairs and Education, concluded a successful official visit to Malaysia on 4th December, solidifying diplomatic ties. During the trip, Dr. Singh engaged in high-level discussions with key Malaysian officials, including V. Sivakumar, the Minister of Human Resources. The visit included the inauguration of the Global Organisation of People of Indian Origin (GOPIO) International Business Summit & Expo, emphasising business ties within the Indian diaspora. Cultural and welfare aspects were also addressed, with Dr. Singh attending 'Bhakti – The Musical' and inaugurating the Indian Workers Resource Centre. Symbolic visits to historic sites underscored the enduring friendship between India and Malaysia, contributing to the ongoing cooperation under the India-Malaysia Enhanced Strategic Partnership.",

