      "Union Minister Meenakshi Lekhi, in a series of engagements with Bulgaria, discussed ways to enhance tourism in bilateral talks with H.E. Mrs. Zaritsa Dinkova, the Minister of Tourism. Her role as Chief Guest at the 'Mala' cultural event, celebrating the 40th anniversary of Indian Studies at Sofia University, showcased India's commitment to cultural ties. In tweets, Minister Lekhi highlighted the importance of people-to-people connections and ancient cultural bonds in the bilateral partnership. Her proactive approach aligns with broader efforts to strengthen diplomatic relations through tourism and cultural understanding. The 'Mala' event serves as a testament to the enduring nature of cultural connections between India and Bulgaria.",

