      'Minister of State for External Affairs, Shri V. Muraleedharan, visited Kenya on November 22-23, fostering diplomatic relations. He held productive meetings with Deputy President Rigathi Gachagua and Cabinet Secretary Rebecca Miano, discussing ways to boost trade and investment. Addressing the India-Kenya Business Forum, he highlighted untapped potential and launched the India-Kenya Business Council. The visit also included commemorating Indian soldiers in East Africa and meeting with Prime Cabinet Secretary Musalia Mudavadi, contributing to the enhancement of bilateral cooperation.',

