    excerpt:
      "India-US 2+2 ministerial dialogue, held on 10th November, marked a significant milestone in the bilateral relations between the two nations. The discussions reflected the enduring commitment to the bilateral partnership and a shared desire to deepen and expand it further. The dialogue comes in the wake of recent high-profile visits, including Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to the US and President Biden's successful trip to India for the G20 summit.\n\nOne of the key themes of the 2+2 dialogue was the comprehensive review of bilateral relations, encompassing various partnerships, including trade and investment, technology, critical and emerging technologies, space cooperation, and mineral security. The officials highlighted the outcomes of recent visits, emphasizing the leadership-driven momentum that has strengthened the Indo-US relationship.\n\nThe regional developments were also a focus of the discussions, with a particular emphasis on growing cooperation in connectivity, such as the India-Middle East-Europe economic corridor. The Quad framework, partnership in the Indo-Pacific, India's leadership in the global south, and the shared challenges faced by both countries were central to the regional dialogue.\n\nThe dialogue also highlighted the robust defence ties between India and the US, mentioning the successful visit of Prime Minister Modi earlier in the year and the continuation of important steps taken during that visit. The defence cooperation was seen as a rock-solid support to the overall bilateral relationship, with discussions covering collaboration in emerging domains for civilian and strategic use.\n\nThe dialogue also addressed specific questions related to defence equipment, including the F-414 engine, MQ-9B drones, and infantry combat vehicles. The Defence Secretary affirmed progress on the commercial arrangement for the F-414 engine, while the MQ-9B drone deal is under consideration. Cooperation on infantry combat vehicles is part of the broader defence industry cooperation roadmap between the two countries.\n\nOn the international front, discussions touched upon the release of eight ex-Navy personnel in Qatar, with India's appeal already filed. The officials emphasized the comprehensive nature of the India-US partnership, encompassing diplomatic, defence, and economic aspects.\n\nThe dialogue highlighted the continued efforts to energize multifaceted India-US cooperation and reaffirmed the commitment to shared objectives and goals. The evening concluded with a call on the Honourable Prime Minister by the four principles on both sides, further reinforcing the strategic partnership between India and the United States. As both nations navigate complex geopolitical challenges, the 2+2 dialogue serves as a testament to the enduring strength and vitality of the Indo-US relationship.",

