      "In a significant diplomatic development, the Foreign Office Consultations (FOC) took place today in New Delhi, jointly chaired by Foreign Secretary Vinay Kwatra from India and Russia's Deputy Foreign Minister, Andrey Rudenko.\n\nThe discussions during the FOC delved into an array of crucial bilateral matters, showcasing the comprehensive nature of the India-Russia relationship. Issues spanning politics, trade, economy, energy, connectivity, defense, and consular affairs were meticulously addressed, reflecting the depth and breadth of their partnership.\n\nBeyond bilateral concerns, the leaders engaged in an exchange of perspectives on regional and global affairs of mutual interest. This diplomatic dialogue further underscores the commitment of both nations to strengthening their ties across diverse domains, reinforcing the enduring friendship between India and Russia. ",

