    excerpt:
      "India's External Affairs Minister, Dr. S Jaishankar, visited the UK from 11th - 15th November. The visit fortified relations with the UK through impactful meetings. Discussions covered diverse topics, signalling a commitment to collaborative solutions in contemporary times.\n\nMeetings with former UK PM Tony Blair and Prime Minister Rishi Sunak emphasized reshaping and enhancing the India-UK relationship. Engagements with UK Foreign Secretary David Cameron covered geopolitical challenges in West Asia, the Ukraine conflict, and the Indo-Pacific region.\n\nProductive talks with UK Defence Secretary Grant Shapps focused on defense and security cooperation, leveraging opportunities through India's ‘Make in India’ initiative. Discussions with UK Home Secretary James Cleverly addressed bilateral cooperation on mobility, skills, and joint efforts against extremism and economic offenses.\n\nAddressing the Indian Community, Dr. Jaishankar highlighted growing momentum in India-UK relations, emphasizing the living bridge and showcasing India's transformative journey. Talks with UK National Security Advisor Tim Barrow delved into pressing global challenges.\n\nEngagements with UK Opposition figures underlined bipartisan support for the India-UK strategic partnership.\n\nIn conclusion, Dr. S Jaishankar's visit strengthened India-UK relations, emphasizing collaboration on global challenges and a shared vision for prosperity and security.",

