      'The 3rd India-Guatemala Foreign Office Consultations (FOC) took place in New Delhi on November 4, with Secretary (East) Saurabh Kumar and Vice Minister Karla Gabriela Samayoa Recari co-chairing the event. The discussions centered on reviewing bilateral ties and fostering deeper collaboration in crucial sectors such as trade, agriculture, health, pharmaceuticals, and development partnerships.\n\nBoth sides emphasized their commitment to strengthening relations and explored avenues for enhanced cooperation within multilateral bodies. The exchange of views on regional and international issues underscored the mutual interest in addressing global challenges and promoting shared values. The meeting marked a significant step in reinforcing the robust and growing relationship between India and Guatemala, paving the way for increased collaboration and mutual prosperity.',

