      '<p>In a significant diplomatic development, H.E. Dr. Zambry Abd Kadir, the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Malaysia, conducted an official visit to India from 05-08 November 2023, accompanied by senior officials of the Malaysian Government.</p><p><br></p><p>On 07 November, Foreign Minister Dr. Zambry held discussions with Vice President Shri Jagdeep Dhankhar, followed by the co-chairing of the 6th India-Malaysia Joint Commission Meeting (JCM) alongside External Affairs Minister, Dr. S. Jaishankar. The JCM conducted a thorough review of bilateral cooperation across various sectors, including political, defense, security, maritime cooperation, trade and investment, health, energy, science and technology, culture, tourism, and people-to-people ties.</p><p><br></p><p>During the JCM, both nations expressed commitment to realizing the Enhanced Strategic Partnership between India and Malaysia. Efforts were pledged to deepen economic and defense engagements, with a focus on emerging areas such as digital public infrastructure, fintech, and semiconductors. Additionally, discussions encompassed regional, multilateral, and geopolitical issues of mutual interest.</p><p><br></p><p>The outcomes of the JCM included the signing/exchanging of:</p><p><br></p><p>(i) Agreed Minutes of the JCM;</p><p>(ii) Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) on Cooperation in Broadcasting between Prasar Bharti, India, and Radio Televisyen Malaysia (RTM), Malaysia; and</p><p>(iii) Notes between Sushma Swaraj Institute of Foreign Service (SSIFS) and Institute of Diplomacy and Foreign Affairs (IDFR) on Cooperation in the Field of Training of Diplomats and Other Personnel.</p>',
