      "Union Minister of State for External Affairs & Culture, Meenakshi Lekhi, embarked on her inaugural visit to the scenic city of Quito, Ecuador, on November 7. The warm reception from the Subsecretary of Asia, Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Human Mobility of Ecuador, marked the beginning of her engaging visit, emphasizing the significance of fostering bilateral relations between India and Ecuador.\n\nDuring her visit, Minister Lekhi highlighted the crucial role of capacity building and development partnership as fundamental pillars of the India-Ecuador relationship. Her productive interaction with ITEC alumni in Ecuador shed light on the positive impact of ITEC courses on their lives, underscoring the successful exchange of knowledge and expertise between the two nations. Minister Lekhi's visit signifies the commitment to further strengthening and expanding the dynamic relationship between India and Ecuador.\n",

